Found the bug. Look at the `HevyWorkout` interface:

```typescript
export interface HevyWorkout {
  id: string;
  short_id: string;
  name: string;  // <-- expects "name"
  ...
}
```

But the Hevy API returns `title`, not `name` — the MCP response shows `"title": "Session A: Shoulder Rehab & Stability"`. So `workout.name` is `undefined`, and the matching callback `(w) => nameToRoutineId.get(w.name)` always returns `undefined`.

Let me confirm by looking at what the raw API actually returns.

